Name: Laish
Description: "They were quiet and unsuspecting"

Name: Aphek
Description: "Its king was among those slain by Joshua."

Name: Baal-Gad
Description: The N-most point of Joshua's conquest of the land of Canaan

Name: Beer-sheba
Description: Means "Well of the Oath" (Or, Well of Seven)

Name: Dor
Description: "Manasseh… proved unable to dispossess the inhabitants... there."

Name: Hepher
Description: "The king… was among those defeated by Joshua"

Name: Jokneam
Description: "A city in Carmel conquered by Joshua."

Name: Kedesh
Description: Assigned to the Gershonites

Name: Taanach
Description: Assigned to the Kohathites. It occupied an important position on at least two trade routes.

Name: Tappuah
Description: "On the boundary between Ephraim and Manasseh."

Name: Arad
Description: One of the most imposing mounds in the region.

Name: Aroer
Description: Situated on the edge of an impressive gorge

Name: Sidon
Description: "and pursued them as far as Great Sidon"

Name: Tirzah
Description: Capital of northern kingdom from reigns of Nabad to Zimri.

Name: Gezer
Description: "its king… tried to save Lachish form the Israelite army"

Name: Lassharon
Description: "A royal Canaanite city"

Name: Madon
Description: "A royal Canaanite city"

Name: Beth-horon
Description: "Strategically situated" Double City

Name: Beth-shemesh
Description: Strategically located. Many wine and olive presses.

Name: Edrei
Description: "A royal city of Og"

Name: Hazor
Description: "had formerly been head of all these kingdoms"

Name: Adullam
Description: The Kingdom of Adullam was one of the 31 kingdoms that were defeated by Joshua.

Name: Bethel
Description: Strategically located and prominent.

Name: Megiddo
Description: "STRATEGICALLY located" "was heavily fortified."
